{"parse":{"title":"Leahy War Victims Fund","pageid":54393231,"revid":791235670,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">Leahy War Victims Fund</caption><tbody><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Abbreviation</th><td class=\"nickname\">\nLWVF</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Successor</th><td>\n<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Marla_Ruzicka_Iraqi_War_Victims_Fund&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Marla Ruzicka Iraqi War Victims Fund (page does not exist)\">Marla Ruzicka Iraqi War Victims Fund</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Formation</th><td class=\"note\">\n1989</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Founder</th><td>\nSenator <a href=\"/wiki/Patrick_J._Leahy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Patrick J. Leahy\">Patrick J. Leahy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\"><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robert_Horvath&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Robert Horvath (page does not exist)\">Robert Horvath</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-usaid_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-usaid-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></th><td>\nManager Programs for Vulnerable Populations</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Parent organization</div></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/USAID\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"USAID\">USAID</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Budget  </div></th><td>\n$10 million per year.<sup id=\"cite_ref-book_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-book-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Leahy War Victims Fund</b> donates prosthetic devices and other rehabilitation services to over 250,000 people with disabilities in 40 countries through the <a href=\"/wiki/US_Agency_for_International_Development\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"US Agency for International Development\">US Agency for International Development</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-us2_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-us2-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Countries_affected\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Countries affected</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leahy_War_Victims_Fund&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 1985, during the <a href=\"/wiki/Contra_War\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Contra War\">Contra War</a>,  Vermont Senator <a href=\"/wiki/Patrick_J._Leahy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Patrick J. Leahy\">Patrick J. Leahy</a> visited the <a href=\"/wiki/Honduras\" title=\"Honduras\">Honduras</a>-<a href=\"/wiki/Nicaraguan\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nicaraguan\">Nicaraguan</a> border on a fact finding tour. He noticed a eleven or twelve year old boy on a crutch with a leg missing because of a landmine. Through a translator, Leahy asked whether the mine the boy triggered had been laid by the <a href=\"/wiki/Sandinista\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sandinista\">Sandinista</a> government or the Contra rebels. The boy had no idea, he just knew his life was ruined forever. After leaving <a href=\"/wiki/Central_America\" title=\"Central America\">Central America</a> Leahy couldn't get the boy out of his mind.<sup id=\"cite_ref-book_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-book-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 1989, the fund was originally established as an earmark to Congressional legislation by Leahy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-usaid_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-usaid-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-un_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-un-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Leahy recounts that when he proposed the fund the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_State_Department\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"United States State Department\">United States State Department</a> and USAID were unenthusiastic and helping war victims was not a foreign policy priority. It was not a \"strategic objective\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-book_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-book-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Initially, the fund emphasized support for people injured by landmines. But over time the program was expanded to include individuals with spinal cord injury, children born with club foot, and individuals with cerebral palsy and a wide range of other conditions that affect mobility or physical function.<sup id=\"cite_ref-usaid_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-usaid-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  \n</p><p>The fund opened up diplomatic relations with <a href=\"/wiki/Vietnam\" title=\"Vietnam\">Vietnam</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-book_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-book-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>To date, the Leahy War Victims Fund has provided nearly $225 million in assistance to more than 50 countries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-un_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-un-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>  As of January 2008, more than $112 million has been disbursed through 19 non-governmental organizations in 28 countries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-book_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-book-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Countries_affected\">Countries affected</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leahy_War_Victims_Fund&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Countries affected\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Sri_Lanka\" title=\"Sri Lanka\">Sri Lanka</a> the program includes the training of Sri Lankans overseas to become physical therapists and prosthetic technicians, introduces polypropylene prosthetic technology to Sri Lanka and expands rehabilitation services to include vocational training, job replacement, peer support and advocacy for mine victims.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leahy_War_Victims_Fund&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-usaid-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-usaid_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-usaid_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-usaid_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.usaid.gov/documents/1866/programs-vulnerable-populations-leahy-war-victims-fund\">Vulnerable Populations Programs: Leahy War Victims Fund Briefer</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/USAID\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"USAID\">USAID</a>, (January 24, 2014).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-book-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-book_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-book_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-book_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-book_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-book_2-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=U8rOKlb7qvsC&amp;pg=PA9&amp;dq=%22leahy+war+victims+fund%22&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjvha3svNrUAhUN9WMKHRmGAaUQ6AEIJDAA#v=onepage&amp;q=%22leahy%20war%20victims%20fund%22&amp;f=false\">Protecting Lives, Restoring Livelihoods: The U.S. Program To Remove Landmines</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=DIANE_Publishing&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"DIANE Publishing (page does not exist)\">DIANE Publishing</a>, (January 2008), Page 9 - 10.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-us2-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-us2_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-us2_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.usaid.gov/what-we-do/democracy-human-rights-and-governance/protecting-human-rights/vulnerable-populations\">VULNERABLE POPULATIONS PROGRAMS</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/USAID\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"USAID\">USAID</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.hrw.org/news/2014/08/04/new-us-landmine-policy-questions-and-answers\">New US Landmine Policy: Questions and Answers</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Human_Rights_Watch\" title=\"Human Rights Watch\">Human Rights Watch</a>, (August 4, 2014).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-un-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-un_5-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-un_5-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">[<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.leahywarvictimsfund.org/\">Leahy War Victims Fund</a> - Unofficial Site</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=7RNgmWnH7KUC&amp;pg=PA26959&amp;dq=%22leahy+war+victims+fund%22&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjAktP3vtrUAhUFMGMKHS3JCisQ6AEIMTAC#v=onepage&amp;q=%22leahy%20war%20victims%20fund%22&amp;f=false\">Congressional Record, V. 144, Pt. 19, October 19, 1998 to December 19, 1998</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.asiantribune.com/index.php?q=node/5199\">Working with INGOs to Eliminate the Threat of Landmines in Sri Lanka</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Asian_Tribune\" title=\"Asian Tribune\">Asian Tribune</a>, (April 4, 2007).</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span c